A retired headmaster has been immortalised in stone - as a gargoyle overlooking his historic old school. 

Dr Richard Shephard was in charge of the Minster School at York Minster for 19 years where the stone caricature was unveiled yesterday. 

He said: 'I don't look on myself as the Hunchback of Notre Dame, but I am very grateful they have done it. It is very thoughtful of people who decided to do it to put it there. 

