'To be honest I was astonished when I heard it was being done, wherever it had gone I would have been delighted, but obviously it is very appropriate.' 

Dr Shephard was also Chamberlain at the Minster and was awarded the MBE for his service. 

He was kept in the dark about the carving but admitted he spotted the resemblance to himself as stonemason Matt Hodgkinson worked on it. 

He added: 'Having oneself immortalised on the Minster as a grotesque may not be to everyone's taste. 

'But I am flattered and honoured that this piece of sculpture has been incorporated into the cathedral that has played such a large part of my life for many years.'

